    ```

5. **Check CORS Configuration**: If your request works via tools like Postman but fails in the browser, CORS issues might be at play. Ensure your Flask server is configured correctly to allow cross-origin requests from your React app's domain and port.

By ensuring email addresses are correctly encoded when passed in URLs and checking the integrity of the request parameters on the server side, you should mitigate issues related to special characters in email addresses. Additionally, refining error handling in both your frontend and backend will make your application more robust and easier to debug.
